# Frontend Structure

The frontend is a React application structured as follows:

## Core Files
- [frontend/src/main.jsx](mdc:frontend/src/main.jsx) - Application entry point
- [frontend/src/App.jsx](mdc:frontend/src/App.jsx) - Main App component
- [frontend/src/index.css](mdc:frontend/src/index.css) - Global styles including Tailwind imports

## Directory Structure
- `src/components/` - Reusable UI components
- `src/pages/` - Page components that represent routes
- `src/routes/` - Routing configuration
- `src/contexts/` - React context providers
- `src/hooks/` - Custom React hooks
- `src/services/` - API service integrations
- `src/utils/` - Utility functions
- `src/layouts/` - Layout components
- `src/styles/` - Additional style files
- `src/config/` - Configuration files

## Development
- Run the development server with `npm run dev` or `yarn dev`
- Build the production version with `npm run build` or `yarn build`
